Business came to a standstill in Kerugoya town on Wednesday after church members protested the death of a form three student. Bishop Francis Wanderi led members of People's Church in street marches over the murder of Meru Boys' student Charles Githaka. Police said robbers broke into Githaka's parents' house last Saturday and hacked him using a jembe. The gangsters stole a TV, DVD player and a woofer. Kirinyaga Central OCPD Yawa Chome said arrests had not been made but that investigations were ongoing.  Wanderi said the church would curse the killers so they never know peace. The Bishop urged police to patrol estates to curb crime. Githaka will be buried in Gichugu constituency on Thursday. Click here for the latest political news